rench Revolution navbox}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Robespierre, Maximilien}}\n[[Category:Maximilien Robespierre| ]]\n[[Category:1758 births]]\n[[Category:1794 deaths]]\n[[Category:French revolutionaries]]\n[[Category:Deputies to the French National Convention]]\n[[Category:Artesian people]]\n[[Category:French deists]]\n[[Category:French jurists]]\n[[Category:French republicans]]\n[[Category:Jacobins]]\n[[Category:French shooting survivors]]\n[[Category:Leaders ousted by a coup]]\n[[Category:Lyc\u00e9e Louis-le-Grand alumni]]\n[[Category:Montagnards]]\n[[Category:French people executed by guillotine during the French Revolution]]\n[[Category:People from Arras]]\n[[Category:Executed revolutionaries]]\n[[Category:Regicides of Louis XVI]]\n[[Category:18th-century French writers]]\n[[Category:18th-century male writers]]\n[[Category:Critics of the Catholic Church]]\n[[Category:People on the Committee of Public Safety]]\n[[Category:People of the Reign of Terror]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the National Convention]]\n[[Category:Critics of atheism]]\n[[Category:18th-century French lawyers]]\n[[Category:Anti-monarchists]]\n[[Category:18th-century jurists]]\n", "name_user": "Taksen", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExecution of Louis XVI:lf", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maximilien_Robespierre"}
{"title_page": "Chief Justice John Marshall", "text_new": "{{Blacklisted-links|1=\n*http://www.geolocation.ws/v/W/4cc151291d41c87f06016718/the-john-marshall-statue-located-in-john/en\n*:''Triggered by <code>\\bgeolocation\\.ws\\b</code> on the local blacklist''|bot=Cyberbot II|invisible=false}}\n{{Infobox artwork\n| image_file =  MarshallWash DC 3.jpg\n| painting_alignment = Front\n| image_size         = 300px\n| title              = Chief Justice John Marshall\n| alt                = \n| other_language_1   = \n| other_title_1      = \n| other_language_2   = \n| other_title_2      = \n| artist             = [[William Wetmore Story]]\n| year               = 1883\n| type               = Bronze\n| height_metric      = \n| width_metric       = \n| length_metric      = 196.9\n| height_imperial    = 75 \n| width_imperial     = 51\n| length_imperial    = {{frac|77|1|2}}\n| metric_unit        = cm\n| imperial_unit      = in\n| city               = [[Northeast, Washington, D.C.]], [[United States]]\n| museum             = \n| coordinates        = \n| owner              = US Supreme Court<br>General Services Administration (recast)<br>Fairmount Park Commission(recast) }}\n'''''Chief Justice John Marshall''''' is a [[bronze sculpture]] of [[John Marshall]], by American sculptor [[William Wetmore Story]]. It is located at the [[United States Supreme Court building|Supreme Court]], 1 First Street, [[Northeast, Washington, D.C.]] It was dedicated on May 10, 1884, by [[Morrison Waite]].<ref>https://archive.org/details/cu31924020622985</ref>\nIt was relocated from the West Terrace, of the [[United States Capitol]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?session=13U50R5310C29.21911&profile=ariall&source=~!siartinventories&view=subscriptionsummary&uri=full=3100001~!4892~!5&ri=7&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ipp=20&spp=20&staffonly=&term=Chief+Justice+John+Marshall,+(sculpture).&index=.TW&uindex=&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ri=7#focus| title= Statue of John Marshall, (sculpture)| publisher=Save Outdoor Sculpture, survey| year= 1993| accessdate=September 3, 2011}}</ref>\n\nThere are two recasts: \n*at [[John Marshall Park]], near [[Judiciary Square]], C Street and 3rd Street, [[Northwest, Washington, D.C.]],{{coord|38.8933|-77.0176}}<ref>{{cite web| url=http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?session=13U50R5310C29.21911&profile=ariall&source=~!siartinventories&view=subscriptionsummary&uri=full=3100001~!322493~!6&ri=3&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ipp=20&spp=20&staffonly=&term=Chief+Justice+John+Marshall,+(sculpture).&index=.TW&uindex=&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ri=3#focus| title=John Marshall: Chief Justice of the United States, (sculpture)| publisher=Save Outdoor Sculpture, District of Columbia survey | year=1993| accessdate=September 3, 2011}}</ref> \n*and at the [[Philadelphia Museum of Art]], 26th Street and the Benjamin Franklin Parkway, [[Philadelphia]].{{coord|39.9662|-75.1818}}<ref>{{cite web| url=http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?session=1S150633847VW.21762&profile=ariall&source=~!siartinventories&view=subscriptionsummary&uri=full=3100001~!15589~!7&ri=7&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ipp=20&spp=20&staffonly=&term=chief+justice+john+marshall&index=.TW&uindex=&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ri=7&limitbox_1=LO01+=+ias#focus| title= Chief Justice John Marshall, (sculpture)| publisher=Save Outdoor Sculpture, Pennsylvania, Philadelphia survey| year= 1993| accessdate=September 3, 2011}}</ref>\n\nThe inscription reads:<br>\nW. W. STORY ROMA 1883 <br>\nJ. ARTHUR LIMERICK CO<br>\nFOUNDERS-BALTO-MD <br>\n(Base, east side:) <br>\nPRESENTED TO THE<br>\nCITY OF PHILADELPHIA<br>\nBY JAMES M. BUCK<br>\n1931 <br>\n(seal of the Fairmount Park Art Association) <br>\n(Base, west side:) <br>\nJOHN MARSHALL<br>\nCHIEF JUSTICE<br>\nOF THE UNITED STATES<br>\n1801\u20131835<br>\nAS SOLDIER HE FOUGHT THAT THE<br>\nNATION MIGHT COME INTO BEING<br>\nAS EXPOUNDER OF THE CONSTITUTION<br>\nHE GAVE IT LENGTH OF DAYS\n\n==See also==\n[[File:Marshall PMA Philly.JPG|thumb|upright=1.1|Philadelphia recast at the [[Philadelphia Museum of Art]]]]\n*[[List of public art in Philadelphia]]\n*[[List of public art in Washington, D.C., Ward 6]]\n\n==References==\n[[File:WWStory-Marshall.jpg|thumb|upright=1.1|Side view at Judiciary Square]]\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Commons category inline}}\n*[http://www.geolocation.ws/v/W/4cc151291d41c87f06016718/the-john-marshall-statue-located-in-john/en Geolocation Judiciary Square recast]{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n{{Public art in Washington, D.C.}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Chief Justice John Marshall}}\n[[Category:1883 sculptures]]\n[[Category:Artworks in the collection of the National Park Service]]\n[[Category:Bronze sculptures in Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:Bronze sculptures in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:Monuments and memorials in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:Outdoor sculptures in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:Sculptures of men in Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:Sculptures of men in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:Statues in Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:Statues in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:John Marshall]]\n\n\n{{public-art-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Blacklisted-links|1=\n*http://www.geolocation.ws/v/W/4cc151291d41c87f06016718/the-john-marshall-statue-located-in-john/en\n*:''Triggered by <code>\\bgeolocation\\.ws\\b</code> on the local blacklist''|bot=Cyberbot II|invisible=false}}\n{{Infobox artwork\n| image_file =  MarshallWash DC 3.jpg\n| painting_alignment = Front\n| image_size         = 300px\n| title              = Chief Justice John Marshall\n| alt                = \n| other_language_1   = \n| other_title_1      = \n| other_language_2   = \n| other_title_2      = \n| artist             = [[William Wetmore Story]]\n| year               = 1883\n| type               = Bronze\n| height_metric      = \n| width_metric       = \n| length_metric      = 196.9\n| height_imperial    = 75 \n| width_imperi