ector; Jenny Bourne is co-editor of ''Race & Class''.\n* [https://www.jewishvoiceforlabour.org.uk/app/uploads/2018/07/OBrien_Comparison-of-IHRA-and-Labour-Party-Definitions-of-Antisemitism.pdf Comparison of IHRA and Labour Party Definitions of Antisemitism], [[Jewish Voice for Labour]], 21 July 2018\n* {{cite journal |title=The text of that speech by Jeremy on the Palestinian ambassador to the UK: English irony and certain Zionist critics |journal=[[Labour Briefing]] |date=29 August 2018 |url=http://labourbriefing.squarespace.com/home/2018/8/29/full-texxt-of-that-speech-by-jeremy-on-zionists-and-a-sense-of-irony |accessdate=12 September 2018 }}\n* {{cite journal |title=Antisemitism: The Far Right, Zionism And The Left  |journal=[[Labour Briefing]] |date=29 August 2018 |url=http://labourbriefing.squarespace.com/home/2018/8/29/full-texxt-of-that-speech-by-jeremy-on-zionists-and-a-sense-of-irony |accessdate=12 September 2018 }}\n* {{cite book |last=Ferguson |first=Rob |title=Antisemitism: The Far Right, Zionism And The Left |year=2019 |publisher=[[Bookmarks (magazine)|Bookmarks]] |isbn=978-19-1292-600-8 |ref=}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Philo|first1=Greg|last2=Berry|first2=Mike|last3=Schlosberg|first3=Justin|last4=Lerman|first4=Antony|last5=Miller|first5=David |url=https://www.plutobooks.com/9780745340661/bad-news-for-labour/|title=Bad News for Labour: Antisemitism, the Party and Public Belief|date=September 2019|publisher=[[Pluto Press]]}}\n* {{cite book|last=Sabbagh|first=Karl|url=https://www.skyscraperpublications.com/the-antisemitism-wars|title=The Antisemitism Wars|date=November 2018|publisher=Skyscraper}}\n* {{cite book|last=Stern-Weiner|first=Jamie (ed)|url= http://v.versobooks.com/Anti-Semitism_and_the_Labour_Party.pdf|title=Anti-Semitism and the Labour Party|date=November 2019|publisher=Verso}}\n\n[[Category:Antisemitism in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Labour Party (UK)]]\n[[Category:Left-wing antisemitism]]\n[[Category:New antisemitism]]\n", "name_user": "Jontel", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200e2020", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antisemitism_in_the_UK_Labour_Party"}
{"title_page": "Bharatiya Janata Party, West Bengal", "text_new": "{{Infobox Indian political party\n| name = Bharatiya Janata Party, West Bengal \n| logo = BJP Election Symbol.svg\n| logo_size = 150px\n| colorcode = {{Bharatiya Janata Party/meta/color}}\n| abbreviation = BJP, West Bengal\n| president = [[Dilip Ghosh (politician)|Dilip Ghosh]]\n| presidium = [[National Executive of Bharatiya Janata Party|State Executive Committee, West Bengal]] <br> {{citation needed|date=April 2020}} \n| headquarters = 6, Muralidhar Sen Lane, [[Kolkata]] - 700073\n| foundation = {{Nowrap|{{Start date and years ago|df=yes|p=y|1980|04|06}}}}<ref name=\":4000\">{{cite news |title=BJP\u2019s foundation day: Brief history of the achievements and failures of the party |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/research/bhartiya-janata-party-narendra-modi-bjp-bjps-37th-foundation-day-brief-history-of-the-achievements-and-failures-of-the-party-4601637/ | accessdate=17 March 2020 |work=The Indian Express |date=6 April 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n| loksabha_seats    = {{Composition bar|18|42|hex=#FF9900}} {{small|(from West Bengal)}}\n| state_seats_name  = [[West Bengal Legislative Assembly]] \n| state_seats       = {{Composition bar|14|295|hex=#FF9933}}\n|website = {{URL|bjpbengal.org}}\n}} \n'''Bharatiya Janata Party, West Bengal''' is a state subsidiary of the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] in [[West Bengal]]. The headquarters is located in [[Kolkata]]. The party appointed [[Dilip Ghosh (politician)|Dilip Ghosh]] as the president of the state unit of the [[BJP]].<ref name=\"hindu\">{{cite news |agency=[[Press Trust of India|PTI]] |title=Dilip Ghosh appointed West Bengal BJP chief. |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/dilip-ghosh-appointed-west-bengal-bjp-chief/article7976954.ece|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|date=11 December 2015|accessdate=20 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/dilip-ghosh-re-elected-west-bengal-bjp-chief/article30578888.ece |title = Dilip Ghosh re-elected West Bengal BJP chief|newspaper = The Hindu|date = 16 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Election History==\n\n\n{{Empty section|date=March 2020}}\n\n==List of Past Presidents==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! No. \n! Name\n! Term in office \n|-\n|1 \n|[[Haripada Bharati]] \n|1980-1982\n|-\n|2\n|[[Vishnu Kant Shastri|Dr. Vishnukant Shastri]] \n|1982-1986\n|-\n|3\n|Sukumar Banerjee\n|1986-1991\n|-\n|4 \n|[[Tapan Sikdar]] \n|1991-1995\n|-\n|(2)\n|[[Vishnu Kant Shastri|Dr. Vishnukant Shastri]] \n|1995-1997\n|-\n|(4)\n|[[Tapan Sikdar]] \n|1997-1999\n|-\n|5\n|Ashim Ghosh\n|1999-2002\n|-\n|6\n|[[Tathagata Roy]] \n|2002-2006\n|-\n|(3)\n|Sukumar Banerjee \n|2006-2008\n|-\n|7\n|[[Satyabrata Mookherjee]] \n|2008-2009\n|-\n|8\n|Rahul Sinha \n|2009-2015\n|-\n|9\n|[[Dilip Ghosh (politician)|Dilip Ghosh]] \n|2015\u2013Present\n|-\n|}\n\n==Organisation and Structure==\n*'''{{large|State President}}''' : [[Dilip Ghosh (politician)|Dilip Ghosh]]\n\n===Morcha Presidents===\n*'''BJYM''' : Debjit Sarkar\n*'''Mahila Morcha''' : [[Locket Chatterjee]] \n*'''S.C. Morcha''' : Arun Halder\n*'''S.T. Morcha''' : Khudiram Tudu \n*'''Kishan Morcha''' : Ramkrishna Pal\n*'''Minority Morcha''' : Ali Hossain\n*'''O.B.C Morcha''' : Swapan Pal\n\n===Departments===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Departments \n! In-Charge \n|-\n|Media Department\n|Saptarshi Chowdhury\n|-\n|Department of Coordination of IT, Website and Social Media Activities\n|Ujjwal Pareek, Joy Mallick\n|-\n|Department of Legal\n|Brajesh Jha\n|-\n|Department for Good Governance\n|Subhash Sarkar, Sanjay Singh\n|-\n|Department for Policy Research\n|Samik Bhattacharya\n|-\n|Media Relations Department\n|Sayantan Basu\n|-\n|Training Department\n|Deepanjan Guha\n|-\n|Department of Political Feedback\n|Jayprakash Majumder\n|-\n|Department of Political Programs & Meetings\n|Pratap Banerjee, Vidyasagar Mantri, Pradip Mishra, Biplab Mitra\n|-\n|Library and Documentation Departments\n|Gopal