= Burbank, CA}}\n}}\n\n{{OWL game log section|Philadelphia Fusion|Season Playoffs (4\u20133)|hide=y|\n{{Overwatch collapsible box|match= Quarterfinals Match 1 |date= July 11 |year=2018|team1= Philadelphia Fusion |team1score=3 |team2score=1 |team2= Boston Uprising |location= Burbank, CA}}\n{{Overwatch collapsible box|match= Quarterfinals Match 2 |date= July 13 |year=2018|team1= Philadelphia Fusion |team1score=1 |team2score=3 |team2= Boston Uprising |location= Burbank, CA}}\n{{Overwatch collapsible box|match= Quarterfinals Match 3 |date= July 13 |year=2018|team1= Philadelphia Fusion |team1score=3 |team2score=1 |team2= Boston Uprising |location= Burbank, CA}}\n{{Overwatch collapsible box|match= Semifinals Match 1 |date= July 18 |year=2018|team1= Philadelphia Fusion |team1score=3 |team2score=1 |team2= New York Excelsior|location= Burbank, CA}}\n{{Overwatch collapsible box|match= Semifinals Match 2 |date= July 21 |year=2018|team1= Philadelphia Fusion |team1score=3 |team2score=2 |team2= New York Excelsior|location= Burbank, CA}}\n{{Overwatch collapsible box|match= Grand Finals Match 1 |date= July 27 |year=2018|team1= Philadelphia Fusion |team1score=1 |team2score=3 |team2= London Spitfire|location= Brooklyn, NY|result=L}}\n{{Overwatch collapsible box|match= Grand Finals Match 2 |date= July 28 |year=2018|team1= Philadelphia Fusion |team1score=0 |team2score=3 |team2= London Spitfire|location= Brooklyn, NY|result=L}}\n}}\n\n{{OWL game log end}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{2018 OWL season by team}}\n{{Philadelphia Fusion}}\n\n[[Category:2018 Overwatch League seasons by team]]\n[[Category:2018 in sports in Pennsylvania|Philadelphia Fusion]]\n[[Category:Philadelphia Fusion seasons]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox OWL season\n| logo =\n| team = Philadelphia Fusion\n| year = 2018\n| record = 24\u201316 ({{winpct|24|16}})\n| division = Atlantic\n| division_place = 4th\n| league_place = 6th\n| coach = Yann Luu\n| owner = [[Comcast Spectacor]]\n| s1playoffs = ''Did not qualify''\n| s2playoffs = [[2018 Overwatch League Season#Playoffs_2|Finals]]\n| s3playoffs = ''Did not qualify''\n| s4playoffs = ''Did not qualify''\n| playoffs = [[2018 Overwatch League Grand Finals|Grand Finals]]\n| OWL allstars = {{Collapsible list\n| title = 2\n| 1 = Carpe (Lee Jae-hyeok)\n| 2 = Poko (Gael Gouzarch)\n}}\n| earnings = $525,000\n| no_prevseason = true\n}}\n\nThe '''2018 Philadelphia Fusion season''' was the first season of the [[Philadelphia Fusion]]'s existence in the [[Overwatch League]]. The team finished with a regular season record of 24\u201316, which was the fifth best in the [[Overwatch League]]. Philadelphia had the same record as the [[London Spitfire]], but London held the tiebreaker by map differential. Philadelphia qualified for the Stage 2 playoffs, in which they lost in the finals against the [[New York Excelsior]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nbcsports.com/philadelphia/nbc-sports-philadelphia/philadelphia-fusion-underdogs-heroes-story-so-far-overwatch-league |title=Philadelphia Fusion: From underdogs to heroes \u2014 the story so far |date=July 26, 2018 |last=Akshon Esports |website=NBC Sports}}</ref> The team also qualified for the Season Playoffs, in which they lost in the [[2018 Overwatch League Grand Finals|Grand Finals]] against the London Spitfire.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/esports/story/_/id/24219415/london-spitfire-wins-inaugural-overwatch-league-title |title=London Spitfire wins inaugural Overwatch League title |date=July 28, 2018 |last=Waltzer |first=Noah |website=ESPN}}</ref>\n\n== Preceding offseason ==\nOn November 3, 2017, Fusion announced their inaugural season roster, consisting of the following players:<ref name=roster1>{{cite web |url=https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20171103005202/en/Philadelphia-Fusion-Players-Coaches-Unveiled |title=Philadelphia Fusion Players and Coaches Unveiled |date=November 3, 2017 |website=Business Wire}}</ref>\n*Lee \"Carpe\" Jae-hyeok\n*Simon \"Snillo\" Ekstr\u00f6m\n*Georgii \"ShaDowBurn\" Gushcha\n*Josue \"Eqo\" Corona\n*Kim \"SADO\" Su-min\n*Joona \"fragi\" Laine\n*Alberto \"Neptuno\" Gonz\u00e1lez Molinillo\n*Park \"DayFly\" Jeong-hwan\n*Joseph \"Joemeister\" Gramano\n*Isaac \"Boombox\" Charles\n*Choi \"Hotba\" Hong-jun\n*Gael \"Poko\" Gouzerch\nDue to \"player logistics issues,\" the Philadelphia Fusion did not participate in preseason play.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/overwatch/overwatch-league-philadelphia-fusion-preseason |title=Philadelphia Fusion will miss the Overwatch League preseason |date=December 5, 2017 |last=Bailey |first=Dustin |website=PC Games}}</ref>\n\n== Review ==\n=== Regular season ===\nPhiladelphia's first regular season OWL match was a 3\u20132 victory against the [[2018 Houston Outlaws season|Houston Outlaws]] on January 11.<ref>{{cite news |last=Carpenter |first=Nicole |title=New York Excelsior, London Spitfire, Philadelphia Fusion impressed fans at Overwatch League day two |date=January 11, 2019 |work=Dot Esports |url=https://dotesports.com/overwatch/news/overwatch-league-day-two-20127 |access-date=March 19, 2019}}</ref> On January 25, Philadelphia upset the undefeated [[2018 New York Excelsior season|New York Excelsior]], which marked New York's only loss in Stage 1.<ref>{{cite news |last=Luongo |first=Cody |title=ESI Gambling Report: Overwatch League Stage 1 Playoffs |date=February 9, 2018 |work=Esports Insider |url=https://esportsinsider.com/2018/02/esi-gambling-report-overwatch-league-stage-1-playoffs/ |access-date=March 18, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Carpenter |first=Nicole |title=Philly Fusion\u2019s win over NYXL proves no one is unbeatable in the Overwatch League |date=January 25, 2018 |work=Dot Esports |url=https://dotesports.com/overwatch/news/philly-fusion-nyxl-upset-owl-jan-25-20538 |access-date=March 19, 2019}}</ref> With a lack of preparation time heading into the regular season, the team struggled for form in [[2018 Overwatch League season#Stage 1|Stage 1]] and would only manage to notch 6 victories, missing the Stage 1 Playoffs.<ref>{{cite news |title=The Final Standings in Stage One of the Overwatch League |date=February 11, 2018 |work=Dexerto |url=https://www.dexerto.com/news/the-final-standings-in-stage-one-of-the-overwatch-league/43920 |access-date=March 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\nUsing the stage-break to catch up on lost practice time and welcoming the arrival of [[Israel|Israeli]] DPS player Josue \"Eqo\" Corana, [[2018 Overwatch League season#Stage 2|Stage 2]] would prove to be a turning point for the team. After opening up the stage with back-to-back sweeps over the [[Boston Uprising]] and [[Florida Mayhem]], the team would continue to impress and go on to achieve a much improved 3rd place finish \u2013 good enough for a stage playoffs berth.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://compete.kotaku.com/phillys-secret-weapon-shines-in-overwatch-league-debut-1823307466|title=Philly's Secret Weapon Shines In Overwatch League Debut|last=Van Allen|first=Eric|date=25 February 2018|work=Compete (Kotaku)|access-date=12 July 2018}}</ref> During the [[2018 Overwatch League season#Playoffs 2|Stage 2 Playoffs]], the team surprised many after defeating heavily favored Stage 1 champions [[London Spitfire]] in the semi-finals, however a finals match-up with the [[New York Excelsior]] would prove a juggernaut too much as the Fusion would fall short in a hard-fought 5-map match.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espn.co.uk/esports/story/_/id/22912064/overwatch-league-stage-2-playoffs-recap|title=New York Excelsior reverse-sweeps Philadelphia Fusion to win Stage 2|last=Nguyen|first=Steven|date=26 March 2018|work=ESPN|access-date=12 July 2018|last2=Craffey|first2=Liam}}</ref>\n\nHeading into the final match of [[2018 Overwatch League season#Stage 3|Stage 3]] on May 5, the Fusion needed a win over the [[2018 Los Angeles Valiant season|Los Angeles Valiant]] for a shot to claim the 4th seed in the Stage 3 playoff bracket. However, the Valiant proved too much to handle, as they defeated the Fusion by a score of 3\u20132 and claimed the 4th seed for their own.<ref>{{cite news |last=O'Brien |first=Joe |title=The Overwatch League Stage 3 Playoff Teams and Bracket are Set |date=May 6, 2018 |work=Dexerto |url=https://www.dexerto.com/overwatch/the-overwatch-league-stage-3-playoff-teams-and-bracket-are-set-76796 |access-date=March 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\nAfter [[2018 Dallas Fuel season|Dallas Fuel's]] upset 3\u20131 win over the Los Angeles Valiant on June 15, Philadelphia needed a 4\u20130 sweep over the [[2018 London Spitfire season|London Spitfire]] in order to make the [[2018 Overwatch League season#Playoffs 4|Stage 4 Playoffs]]. While the Fusion were victorious in that matchup, they were only able to win by a score of 3\u20131 and subsequently, missed the Stage 4 Playoffs.<ref>{{cite news |last=Lingle |first=Samuel |title=Dallas Fuel will play in OWL stage 4 title matches after Philadelphia Fusion fail to sweep London Spitfire |date=June 16, 2018 |work=Dot Esports |url=https://dotesports.com/overwatch/news/philadelphia-fusion-dallas-fuel-stage-four-title-matches-owl-24924 |access-date=March 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Season playoffs ===\nPhiladelphia Fusion claimed the 6th seed in the Season Playoffs on June 15, after [[2018 Seoul Dynasty season|Seoul Dynasty]] lost to the [[2018 Los Angeles Gladiators season |Los Angeles Gladiators]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Lingle |first=Samuel |title=Seoul Dynasty\u2019s loss cedes an OWL playoff spot to Philadelphia Fusion |date=June 15, 2018 |work=Dot Esports |url=https://dotesports.com/overwatch/news/seoul-dynasty-eliminated-owl-playoffs-24898 |access-date=March 19, 2019}}</ref> During the Post-Season Playoffs, Philadelphia Fusion first faced the Boston Uprising. After a dominant first game they lost the second one, forcing a tie-breaker game which Fusion managed to win. After that they faced the New York Excelsior, who were heavy favorites to win the Post-Season playoffs. Fusion upset them in the first game, winning 3\u20130 and then narrowly winning the second game 3\u20132, which sent them to the grand finals. In the Grand Finals they faced another underdog; the London Spitifire. The Spitfire however showed the potential their team had and beat the Fusion in a best of 3 game series, winning 2\u20130.<ref>{{cite news |last=Waltzer |first=Noah |title=London Spitfire wins inaugural Overwatch League title |publisher=ESPN |date=28 July 2018 |url=http://www.espn.com/esports/story/_/id/24219415/london-spitfire-wins-inaugural-overwatch-league-title |access-date=18 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Bright |first=Ryan |title=London Spitfire duo master Philadelphia Fusion to claim first Overwatch League title |date=28 July 2018 |publisher=NBC Sports |url=https://www.nbcsports.com/philadelphia/nbc-sports-philadelphia/london-spitfire-duo-master-philadelphia-fusion-claim-first-overwatch-league |access-date=18 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Final roster ==\n{{OWL roster header|team=Philadelphia Fusion|season=2018}}\n<!-- list of players -->\n{{OWL player | num = 3 | handle = snillo | first = Simon | last = Ekstr\u00f6m | role = Damage | nat=SWE | prev_team=123}}\n{{OWL player | num = 13 | handle = ShaDowBurn | first = Georgii | last = Gushcha | role = Damage | nat=RUS | prev_team=[[FaZe Clan]]}}\n{{OWL player | num = 15 | handle = Eqo | first = Josue | last = Corona | role = Damage | nat=Israel | prev_team=Zengaming eSports}}\n{{OWL player | num = 18 | handle = Carpe | name = Lee Jae-hyeok | role = Damage | nat=KOR | prev_team=[[FaZe Clan]]}}\n{{OWL player | num = 9 | handle = SADO | name = Kim Su-min | role = Tank | nat=KOR | prev_team=''N/A''}}\n{{OWL player | num = 54 | handle = Fragi | first = Joona | last = Laine | role = Tank | nat=FIN | prev_team=Team Gigantti}}\n{{OWL player | num = 8 | handle = neptuNo | first = Alberto | last = Gonz\u00e1lez | role = Support | nat=ESP | prev_team=[[Cloud9|Cloud9 EU]]}}\n{{OWL player | num = 10 | handle = DayFly | name = Park Jeong-hwan | role = Support | nat=KOR | prev_team=Ardeont}}\n{{OWL player | num = 23 | handle = Joemeister | first = Joseph | last = Gramano | role = Support | nat=CAN | prev_team=[[FaZe Clan]]}}\n{{OWL player | num = 42 | handle = Boombox | first = Isaac | last = Charles | role = Support | nat=ENG | prev_team=eUnited}}\n{{OWL player | num = 7 | handle = HOTBA | name = Choi Hong-jun | role = Flex | nat=KOR | prev_team=LW Red}}\n{{OWL player | num = 21 | handle = Poko | first = Gael | last = Gouzerch | role = Flex | nat=FRA | prev_team=GamersOrigin}}\n<!--end of list players-->\n{{OWL roster footer\n| head_coach =\n*Yann Luu\n| roster_url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180802052746/https://overwatchleague.com/en-us/players\n| accessdate = November 3, 2017\n}}\n\n== Standings ==\n=== Record by stage ===\n{| class=\"toccolours\" border=0 cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:95%; text-align:left; width:700px;\"\n|- align=\"left\" style=\"background:#{{OWL color|PHI|1}}; color:#{{OWL color|PHI|2}};\"\n! style=\"width:75px\" | Stage !! {{abbr|Pld|Matches played}} !! {{abbr|W|Wins}} !! {{abbr|L|Losses}} !! {{abbr|Pct|Winning percentage}} !! {{abbr|MW|Maps won}} !! {{abbr|ML|Maps lost}} !! {{abbr|MT|Maps tied}} !! {{abbr|MD|Map differential}} !! {{abbr|Pos|Position in league}}\n|-\n|colspan = \"10\" |\n|-\n| 1 || 10 || 6 || 4 || {{winpct|6|4}} || 20 || 24 || 1 || -4 || 7\n|-style=\"background:#cfc\"\n| 2 || 10 || 7 || 3 || {{winpct|7|3}} || 27 || 15 || 0 || +12 || 3\n|-\n| 3 || 10 || 5 || 5 || {{winpct|5|5}} || 24 || 23 || 0 || +1 || 7\n|-\n| 4 || 10 || 6 || 4 || {{winpct|6|4}} || 22 || 18 || 1 || +4 || 6\n|-style=\"background-color:#cfc\"\n! Overall !! 40 !! 24 !! 16 !! {{winpct|24|16}} !! 93 !! 80 !! 2 !! +13 !! 6\n|-\n| colspan=\"10\" |\n|- style=\"background:#EAECF0;\"\n| colspan=\"10\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | {{legend inline|#bfb|Qualified for playoffs}}\n|}\n\n=== League ===\n{{2018 Overwatch League standings}}\n\n== Game log ==\n=== Regular season ===\n{{OWL game log start|Philadelphia Fusion|2018|wins=24|losses=16}}\n\n{{OWL game log section|Philadelphia Fusion|Stage 1 (6\u20134)|hide=y|\n{{Overwatch collapsible box|match=1|date= January 11 |year=2018|team1= Philadelphia Fusion |team1score=3 |team2score=2 |team2= Houston Outlaws |location= Burbank, CA}}\n{{Overwatch collapsible box|match=2|date= January 13 |year=2018|team1= London Spitfire |team1score=4 |team2score=0 |team2= Philadelphia Fusion |location= Burbank, CA}}\n{{Overwatch collapsible box|match=3|date= January 17 |year=2018|team1= San Francisco Shock |team1score=1 |team2score=2 |team2= Philadelphia Fusion |location= Burbank, CA}}\n{{Overwatch collapsible box|match=4|date= January 18 |year=2018|team1= Philadelphia Fusion |team1score=2 |team2score=3 |team2= Los Angeles Gladiators |location= Burbank, CA}}\n{{Overwatch collapsible box|match=5|date= January 25 |year=2018|team1= Philadelphia Fusion |team1score=3 |team2score=2 |team2= New York Excelsior |location= Burbank, CA}}\n{{Overwatch collapsible box|match=6|date= January 26 |year=2018|team1= Shanghai Dragons |team1score=2 |team2score=3 |team2= Philadelphia Fusion |location= Burbank, CA}}\n{{Overwatch collapsible box|match=7|date= January 31 |year=2018|team1= Los Angeles Valiant |team1score=4 |team2score=0 |team2= Philadelphia Fusion |location= Burbank, CA}}\n{{Overwatch collapsible box|match=8|date= February 01 |year=2018|team1= Philadelphia Fusion |team1score=4 |team2score=0 |team2= Dallas Fuel |location= Burbank, CA}}\n{{Overwatch collapsible box|match=9|date= February 08 |year=2018|team1= Philadelphia Fusion |team1score=0 |team2score=4 |team2= Boston Uprising |location= Burbank, CA}}\n{{Overwatch collapsible box|match=10|date= February 10 |year=2018|team1= Florida Mayhem |team1score=2 |team2score=3 |team2= Philadelphia Fusion |location= Burbank, CA}}\n}}\n\n{{OWL game log section|Philadelphia Fusion|Stage 2 (7\u20133)|hide=y|\n{{Overwatch collapsible box|match=11|date= February 22 |year