t Championship#Title history|3 times]])<ref name=\"NWAPNWH1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wrestling-titles.com/us/pnw/nwa/pnw-h.html|title=NWA Pacific Northwest Heavyweight Championship History at Wrestling-Titles.com|accessdate=October 11, 2007}}</ref>\n** [[NWA Pacific Northwest Tag Team Championship]] ([[NWA Pacific Northwest Tag Team Championship#Title history|3 times]]) \u2013 with Top Gun (1), The Grappler (1), and Steve Doll (1)<ref name=\"NWAPNWTT1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wrestling-titles.com/us/pnw/nwa/pnw-t.html|title=NWA Pacific Northwest Tag Team Championship History at Wrestling-Titles.com|accessdate=October 11, 2007}}</ref>\n** [[NWA Pacific Northwest Television Championship]] ([[NWA Pacific Northwest Television Championship#Title history|1 time]])<ref name=\"NWAPNWT1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wrestling-titles.com/us/pnw/nwa/pnw-tv.html|title=NWA Pacific Northwest Television Championship History at Wrestling-Titles.com|accessdate=October 11, 2007}}</ref>\n* '''[[Pro-Pain Pro Wrestling]]'''\n** [[Pro-Pain Pro Wrestling#3PW World Heavyweight Championship|3PW World Heavyweight Championship (1 time)]]<ref name=\"3PWH3\">{{cite web|url= http://www.solie.org/titlehistories/htpppw.html|title=3PW World Heavyweight Championship History at Solie.org|accessdate=October 11, 2007}}</ref>\n* '''''[[Pro Wrestling Illustrated]]'''''\n** Ranked No. 22 of the top 500 singles wrestlers in the ''[[Pro Wrestling Illustrated#PWI 500|PWI 500]]'' in 2003<ref>{{cite web|url=http://profightdb.com/pwi-500/2003.html|title=Pro Wrestling Illustrated (PWI) 500 for 2003|publisher=The Internet Wrestling Database|accessdate=August 25, 2015}}</ref>\n** Ranked No. 168 of the top 500 singles wrestlers in the \"PWI Years\" in 2003<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.100megsfree4.com/wiawrestling/pages/pwi/pwi500yr.htm|accessdate=September 6, 2010|title=Pro Wrestling Illustrated Top 500 \u2013 PWI Years|publisher=Wrestling Information Archive|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110707054220/http://www.100megsfree4.com/wiawrestling/pages/pwi/pwi500yr.htm|archivedate=July 7, 2011}}</ref>\n*'''''Ring Around The Northwest Newsletter'''''\n**Wrestler of the Year (1989\u20131990)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kayfabememories.com/Regions/pnw/pnw16-2.htm |title=Regional Territories: PNW #16 Page #2 |author=Rodgers, Mike |date=2004 |website=KayfabeMemories.com |publisher= |accessdate=}}</ref>\n* '''[[Total Nonstop Action Wrestling]]'''\n** [[NWA World Heavyweight Championship]] ([[List of NWA World Heavyweight Champions|1 time]])<ref name=\"NWAWH2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wrestling-titles.com/nwa/world/nwa-h.html|title=NWA World Heavyweight Championship History at Wrestling-Titles.com|accessdate=October 11, 2007}}</ref>\n** [[King of the Mountain match|King of the Mountain]] ([[King of the Mountain match|2005]])<ref name=\"KOTM2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.onlineworldofwrestling.com/results/tnappv/slammiversary05.html|title=TNA Slammiversary 2005 Pay Per View results at Online World of Wrestling|accessdate= October 11, 2007}}</ref>\n** [[TNA Gauntlet for the Gold|Gauntlet for the Gold]] ([[TNA Gauntlet for the Gold#List of Gauntlet for the Gold winners|2003]] \u2013 Heavyweight)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cagematch.net/?id=1&nr=1432|title=NWA-TNA Weekly PPV 59 results |website=Cagematch |accessdate=February 27, 2020}}</ref>\n* '''United States Xtreme Wrestling'''\n** UXW Heavyweight Championship (4 times)<ref name=\"USXWH1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.uxwwrestling.net/titlehistory.html#xtreme|title=USXW Heavyweight Championship History at UXW Wrestling.net|accessdate=October 11, 2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071012013522/http://uxwwrestling.net/titlehistory.html#xtreme|archivedate=October 12, 2007}}</ref>\n* '''[[United States Wrestling Association]]'''\n** [[USWA World Tag Team Championship]] ([[USWA World Tag Team Championship#Title history|1 time]]) \u2013 with [[Brian Lawler|Brian Christopher]]<ref name=\"USWATT2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wrestling-titles.com/us/tn/uswa/uswa-t.html|title=USWA Tag Team Championship History at Wrestling-Titles.com|accessdate=October 11, 2007}}</ref>\n* '''United States Wrestling Organization'''\n** USWO Heavyweight Championship (1 time)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cagematch.net/?id=5&nr=682|title=USWO Heavyweight Championship History}}</ref>\n* '''USA Pro Wrestling'''\n** USA Pro Heavyweight Championship (1 time)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.onlineworldofwrestling.com/results/other/2003-05.html|title=Independent Wrestling Results \u2013 May 2003|accessdate=July 5, 2008|publisher=Online World of Wrestling}}</ref>\n* '''Vanguard Championship Wrestling'''\n** VCW Heavyweight Championship (1 time)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cagematch.net/?id=5&nr=2334|title=VCW Heavyweight Championship History}}</ref>\n* '''[[World Championship Wrestling]]'''\n** [[WCW Light Heavyweight Championship]] ([[WCW Light Heavyweight Championship#Title history|1 time]])<ref name=\"WCWLH2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wrestling-titles.com/wcw/wcw-lh.html|title=WCW Light Heavyweight Championship History at Wrestling-Titles.com|accessdate=October 11, 2007}}</ref>\n** [[WWE United States Heavyweight Championship|WCW United States Heavyweight Championship]] ([[List of WWE United States Champions|1 time]])<ref name=\"WCWUS2\">{{cite web|url= http://www.wrestling-titles.com/wcw/wcw-us-h.html|title=WCW United States Heavyweight Championship History at Wrestling-Titles.com|accessdate=October 11, 2007}}</ref>\n** [[WCW World Tag Team Championship]] ([[List of WCW World Tag Team Champions|1 time]]) \u2013 with [[Perry Saturn]]<ref name=\"WCWWTT2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wrestling-titles.com/wcw/wcw-t.html|title=WCW World Tag Team Championship History at Wrestling-Titles.com|accessdate=October 11, 2007}}</ref>\n* '''[[WWE|World Wrestling Federation/Entertainment]]'''\n** [[WWE Hardcore Championship|WWF/E Hardcore Championship]] ([[List of WWE Hardcore Champions|27 times]])<ref name=\"WWEH4\"